<blockquote>
<p>It reads like a cheesy anime fight, where the characters aren't so much fighting or outsmarting each other as asspulling secret techniques and powers, and that just doesn't do anything for me. Not much of a fan of urban fantasy style things, either, but that's personal taste and not a criticism.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This is why I upvoted. Sometimes, people don't win because they're <em>good</em> at what they're doing, or the <em>good guys</em>, or even through careful planning and good teamwork. Sometimes, people win by being high as balls, crazy as a shithouse rat, and obscenely lucky to boot. Those are the true underdog stories: the kind of people who live lives that seem less like reality and more like dipshit, goofy, ridiculous Grand Theft Auto mods. When those people win, they deserve applause simply because their victory was so damn unlikely.</p>

